# Windsurf Rules — Trading Exchange Platform

## Project Overview
Microservices crypto trading platform. Maven multi-module parent `crypto-exchange` with five Spring Boot 3 / Java 21 services and a React 18 + TypeScript frontend.

## Module Structure
```
auth/           → Authentication Service     (port 8081, org.serhiileniv.auth)
gateway/        → API Gateway                (port 8080, org.serhiileniv.gateway)
order-matching/ → Order Matching Service     (port 8082, org.serhiileniv.order)
wallet/         → Wallet Service             (port 8083, org.serhiileniv.wallet)
market-data/    → Market Data Service        (port 8084, org.serhiileniv.marketdata)
frontend/       → React SPA                  (port 3000, exchange-ui)
```

## Naming Conventions

### Java
- Packages: `org.serhiileniv.<module>` — no `crypto` prefix inside packages
- Main classes: `AuthApplication`, `GatewayApplication`, `OrderMatchingApplication`, `WalletApplication`, `MarketDataApplication`
- Services: `UserService`, `WalletService`, `OrderService`, `MarketDataService`
- Repositories: extend `JpaRepository`, suffix `Repository`
- DTOs: suffix `Request` or `Response` — e.g. `OrderRequest`, `WalletResponse`
- Events: `OrderPlacedEvent`, `OrderMatchedEvent`, `OrderCancelledEvent` — always include `eventType` STRING field
- Controllers: `@RequestMapping("/api/v1/<resource>")` prefix

### Spring app names
- `auth-service`, `api-gateway`, `order-matching-service`, `wallet-service`, `market-data-service`

### Kafka
- Topic: `order-events`
- Consumer groups: `wallet-group`, `market-data-group`
- `eventType` values: `ORDER_PLACED`, `ORDER_MATCHED`, `ORDER_CANCELLED`

### Docker containers
- Services: `auth-service`, `api-gateway`, `order-matching-service`, `wallet-service`, `market-data-service`
- Infrastructure: `postgres`, `redis-auth`, `redis-market`, `kafka`, `zookeeper`, `pgadmin`

### Frontend
- Components/pages: PascalCase — `PlaceOrderPage`, `ToastContext`
- API functions: camelCase — `placeOrder`, `getWallets`
- Types: PascalCase interfaces — `OrderResponse`, `WalletResponse`

## Architecture Decisions

### Request flow
1. Browser → nginx (port 3000) → nginx proxies `/api/*` → gateway (port 8080)
2. Gateway validates JWT → injects `X-User-Id` header → forwards to service
3. Services read user from `X-User-Id` header, never re-parse JWT themselves

### Security
- JWT: HMAC-SHA, access token 15 min, refresh token 7 days
- `JWT_SECRET_KEY` must match in: gateway, auth, order-matching, wallet
- Refresh tokens stored in Redis, revoked on logout
- Frontend: access token in JS memory only; refresh token in localStorage

### Order lifecycle
```
POST /api/v1/orders
  → persist Order (PENDING)
  → publish OrderPlacedEvent → Kafka order-events
  → matchOrder() synchronously
  → publish OrderMatchedEvent (if matched)
```

### Wallet saga (Kafka-driven)
- `ORDER_PLACED` → lock funds
- `ORDER_MATCHED` → settle (debitLocked payer, deposit receiver)
- `ORDER_CANCELLED` → unlock funds
- All events checked against ProcessedEvent table for idempotency

### Market data
- Updated on every ORDER_MATCHED event
- Redis cache with 10-minute TTL, evicted on trade
- 24h stats reset daily at midnight UTC

## Code Standards

### Java
- Lombok: `@Data @Builder @RequiredArgsConstructor @Slf4j`
- `@Transactional` on all service write methods
- Never expose JPA entities from controllers — always map to DTOs
- Tests: Mockito mocks only (no embedded DB). Set `eventType` in all Kafka test fixtures.

### Frontend
- API errors: read `err.userMessage` (set by Axios interceptor)
- Mutations: always invalidate affected React Query cache keys on success
- No hardcoded API base URLs — use `VITE_API_BASE_URL` env var

## Build
```bash
mvn -B clean verify          # build + test all modules
mvn -B test -pl wallet       # single module
docker compose up --build    # full stack
```

## Never Break
- JWT_SECRET_KEY identical in 4 services
- Kafka events always have `eventType` field
- Wallet consumer always checks ProcessedEvent before acting
- Lombok before MapStruct in annotationProcessorPaths
